    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="562"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79682/23a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Walton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-09T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 9, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Pan American Airways representative in Liberia is being instructed to proceed
                    immediately with the signing of its initialed contract for commercial
                        services.<note n="17" xml:id="d562fn17">Contract signed on July 14,
                        1941.</note> You should offer your good services in this connection if it
                    should appear necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
